{
  "texts": [
    "Such models are almost exclusively trained using first-order optimization algorithms (e.g., gradient descent), which proceed iteratively over T iterations.",
    "Start- ing from initial parameters (0), the optimizer returns at the end of each iteration, t ∈ [T], updated model parameters (t), where (t) is generated from previous parameters (t-1), loss function, batch B (t) ⊆ D, learning rate 𝜂 (t) > 0, and weight decay (L 2) strength ≥ 0.",
    "Training gradients are denoted ∇ L(z i; (t)).",
    "The training set's empirical risk Hessian for iteration t is denoted",
    ", with the corresponding inverse risk Hessian denoted (H (t)) -1."
  ]
}